# LAOS local .env
#
# Copy to `.env` (or run setup.ps1 which does it for you).
# Never commit `.env`.
#
# Variables here are referenced from .opencode/opencode.jsonc via {env:NAME}.

# ─── GitHub ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GITHUB_TOKEN is NOT set here. Set it as an OS environment variable
# (System Properties > Environment Variables on Windows, or in your
# profile shell init). opencode reads from process env.
#
# Why OS env instead of .env: GITHUB_TOKEN is used across all your
# projects; putting it once in OS env beats duplicating in every .env.

# ─── Exa ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Exa MCP uses OAuth on first connection. No key needed here.

# ─── Context7 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. Free tier works without a key. Get a key for higher
# rate limits at https://context7.com/dashboard
# CONTEXT7_API_KEY=

# ─── N8N (local self-hosted) ──────────────────────────────────
# Required for the `n8n-community` MCP (kept disabled by default).
#
# First-run steps:
#   1. In another terminal: `npx n8n` (or use your existing local install).
#   2. Open http://localhost:5678 and create your owner account.
#   3. Settings > n8n API > enable the API and create a key.
#   4. Paste the key below.
#   5. Set "enabled": true for the n8n-community MCP in opencode.jsonc.
N8N_API_URL=http://localhost:5678/api/v1
N8N_API_KEY=
